This corridor has the feel of something deliberately dug rather than naturally formed — the walls are too regular, the ceiling too consistent, the floor too flat.  Someone shaped this passage with tools, though long ago enough that the bioluminescent fungi have colonised the lower walls and the ceiling has taken on the spotted texture of advanced root-penetration.  The passage smells more strongly of the upper forest here, a preview of the surface that grows stronger with every step east.~
