#1033
The Threshold Passage~
The underground passage reaches its final stretch here, the ceiling lowering slightly as the earth above grows shallower.  Root-tendrils penetrate the ceiling in dense clusters and hang down to shoulder height, requiring navigation on the way through.  The floor is slightly damp here, moisture seeping in from the soil above, and small shelf fungi have taken up residence on every root.  The passage smells unmistakably of open air — a complex, organic freshness utterly unlike the enclosed and stale underground atmosphere left behind.~
