#1034
The Briar Threshold~
The underground passage ends here in a chamber whose eastern wall is not earth but a dense mass of living roots and @@pthorn-laced brambles@@N — the buried root-systems of the briar maze above, which have grown downward to meet the mycelium network of the hollows in an underground tangle.  The brambles are alive and apparently aware: they shift slightly when approached, their thorns angling outward.  A gap barely wide enough for a person to pass through has been worn through the briar mass by repeated passage, the thorns along its edges polished smooth by contact with skin and armour.  The sound of wind — impossible this far underground — drifts through the gap.~
