#1035
A Thorn-Choked Trail~
The undergrowth here has become something else entirely — not plants growing in soil but a three-dimensional lattice of thorned vines so densely interwoven that the ground beneath them is invisible, the sky above concealed, and the space between containing only more thorns, their tips catching the diffuse light from every angle.  There is no clear path, and yet there are worn channels between the vines that suggest passage is possible in several directions, if one accepts the certainty of being scratched and the impossibility of keeping one's bearings.  A sound that might be the maze breathing drifts from the west, and something small and many-legged retreats from the nearest vine-cluster.~
