#1036
The Briar Canopy Path~
The thorn-vines here have grown taller and arched overhead to form a tunnel of interlaced brambles, creating a green-dark corridor with a roof of thorns that catches occasional glimpses of the sky in tiny irregular patches.  The walls of the tunnel are in constant slow motion — individual vines shifting their growth by fractions that add up, over hours, to significant repositioning — which means the corridor's exact dimensions are never quite the same twice.  Scratched into the largest thorn-stem at head height, just legible: a single arrow pointing south, and below it, another arrow pointing in an entirely different south.~
