#1037
The Weeping Thorn Hollow~
This broader space has a quality of being a room rather than a corridor — the vines here have grown outward from a central point rather than along a line, creating a roughly spherical void in the briar mass.  The thorns are covered in drops of amber fluid that never fall, caught on each thorn-tip and glinting in the diffuse light like a jewelled chandelier.  The amber smells of nothing — it has no scent, which in the context of this organic, living place is more unsettling than any smell could be.  The void in the briar feels intentional, as if maintained by something with an interest in keeping this particular space clear.~
