The Scratching Chamber~
The sound of thorns scraping against each other fills this section of the maze — a continuous, multidirectional scratching that appears to have no specific source and does not change in response to the traveller's own movements.  The vines here move more visibly than elsewhere in the maze, not the slow growth-shift seen before but a faster, jerky repositioning as if the brambles are restless.  The floor between the vine-stems is scattered with pale objects that resolve, on closer inspection, into bone fragments — small creatures, mostly, reduced to component pieces by thorns or time or both.~
