#1041
The Vine Confluence~
Several thorn-channels converge here, their meeting creating a space slightly larger than the surrounding maze — perhaps large enough to turn around in without snagging.  The vines that form each channel's walls lock into each other at the junction in elaborate interweavings, and the thorn arrangement at the interlocking points has a look of negotiation — as though each branch-line agreed to a specific crossing pattern.  There is something pinned to the nearest vine at eye height: a piece of leather, torn from something larger, bearing a burnt-in mark that might be a map of the maze — but if so, it shows neither where you are now nor any exit.~
