#1044
The Thornweaver's Gallery~
The thorn-vines here have been shaped — not by any tool but by the consistent efforts of multiple generations of large spiders whose webs fill the space between every vine in thick, three-dimensional sheets.  The webs are not the light silk of common spiders but something heavier, thorn-laced with debris caught over months of operation, forming impermeable screens that subdivide the passage into sub-channels.  Where the webbing is thickest, it has the structural integrity of felt, and things are caught in it — shed skins of large arthropods, desiccated prey, and at one point what appears to be a gauntlet, still with something inside it.~
