The Low Archway Chamber~
Two vine-arches stand in sequence here, each smaller than the last, creating a perspective-compressing corridor that seems to diminish the far end to a pinpoint.  The arches are ancient — the thorns on them are massive, some as long and thick as fingers, and their tips have developed a dark crystalline coating that suggests years of accumulated mineral deposit from the amber and clear fluids that drip throughout the maze.  Between the arches, the ground has been worn to bare earth by countless passages, and the surrounding vines are bent outward by the pressure of something that has squeezed through this bottleneck many times at a considerable size.~
