The Thorn Parliament~
This section of the maze is wider than any encountered so far, a roughly oval clearing where the vines have grown back from a central space and left a genuine open area — perhaps thirty feet across — with the night sky clearly visible overhead.  But the clearing is not empty: the thorn-vines that form its border are extremely tall here, and from their upper reaches hang dozens of dried shapes that were once living things.  The shapes vary in size from small creatures to something approaching human proportions.  Whatever the Briar Maze considers parliament, it appears to involve displayed trophies.~
