The Parallel Runs~
The vine-walls here have been shaped into deliberate parallel channels running east to west, each just wide enough for a person, separated by solid walls of compressed thorn-growth.  The effect is of a series of corridors running side by side, with no visible connection between them — but the maze being what it is, stepping sideways sometimes achieves different results than the geometry suggests.  Desiccated insects and small animals lie at regular intervals in each run, as though placed there — offerings, perhaps, or points in a game the maze is playing against itself.~
