The Convergence Point~
The multiple channels of the maze all seem to funnel toward this point — a larger space where routes that appeared to run parallel suddenly meet, their vine-walls merging into a single mass that forces everything into one shared path before the maze decides to split again.  The junction is marked by an enormous thorn-stem, a single vine thicker than a person's torso that rises from the centre of the convergence and disappears overhead into the canopy.  The stem is covered in deep scratches that do not correspond to thorn-marks — they are too regular, too parallel, and cut too deep into living wood to be incidental.~
